race.comment: SUPIDO EXPRESS (1) is knocking on the door of another win, going under in a photo finish his past couple, the latest in Saturday company. Back to a CL1 now and while he's up in the weights he brings very strong form into this. Draws ideally and strikes very winnable race. TERRITORY MAN (2) won on debut before missing as favourite at Ascot back in February. He'll be fitter for two trials coming in and Pike remains in the irons from his trials. Should get a lovely run on the map and he'll make his presence felt fresh. FLASH DANCER (6) was too good first-up at this 1200m when sitting on the speed as favourite. While the draw may be a niggle, the slight rise in trip is not and he looks a progressive type. Can build on what he did last time out. TOUSLED CROWN (11) just missed fresh over this course and distance and has to be included on that performance. SALTY MISS (3) flew late to be 1L away last stat in the same race as SUPIDO EXPRESS. Not out of this.
